<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870619-0122 </DOCNO><HL> Shawmut Buys Back Shares</HL><DD> 06/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SHASBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><DATELINE> BOSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Shawmut Corp. said it bought a block of 400,000 common shares from a broker it didn't disclose. The bank holding company said the shares will be kept in its treasury.    The company said it believes the stock is &quot;undervalued.&quot; It called the price, which it didn't disclose, &quot;a bargain.&quot;    Shawmut has about 16.1 million shares outstanding. Shawmut shares closed at $46.625, down 37.5 cents, in national over-the-counter trading yesterday. </TEXT></DOC>